node.title: Police name Gisborne toddler who died from critical injuries
node.description: Police continue to appeal for information as a homicide investigation into the 19-month-old's death is ongoing.
node.content:
["Police have named the Gisborne toddler who died last month as a result of critical injuries.", "", "
\nPhoto: RNZ / Richard Tindiller\n
", "Casino Ataria Wharehinga died in Starship Hospital on 10 January 2022", "Police continue to appeal for information as a homicide investigation into the 19-month-old's death is ongoing.", "They said the toddler suffered the critical injuries at a residential address in Te Hapara, Gisborne.", "\"This is a tragic start to 2022 - I would encourage anyone with information, even if they think it might not be relevant, to please come forward,\" said detective senior sergeant Sally Patrick.", "People can call Gisborne Police via 105 and refer to file number 220106/5689 or call Crime Stoppers anonymously on 0800 555 111."]
